The forces of the giant strike are gathering
The League Unions and the National Federation of Workers' Commissions will set up a strike commission on Friday to coordinate the Monday strike that will last indefinitely.
On Saturday there will be a protest rally, while on Monday - the day on which the final vote on the public health law will be held - there will be work stoppage.
This action will certainly cause great difficulties in transport, as rail transit will be completely stopped and the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company will also be on strike until 1 p.m.
On Friday afternoon, the League Unions will report on the details of their Monday strike that will be held jointly with the National Federation of Workers' Commissions.
The strike commission of the LIGA and the National Union of Engineers will also be set up to coordinate Monday's actions.
A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while on Monday the participating unions will strike indefinitely, if no agreement is reached with the government.
This means that - on the day of the parliamentary vote on the public health law - they did not report on the date of the end of the strike started.
If the National Assembly disapprove of the public health law, trade unions will immediately withdraw their call for strike.
On the other hand, if the law is passed, strike commissions will meet and decide on the future.
On the basis of the National Assembly's Monday agenda, it is also possible that only the public health law will be voted on during the very late hours of the night, or perhaps near midnight.
As a result of the strike that will start on Monday, there will have to be significant difficulties in transport: on the railways it will stop working indefinitely, in the morning a part of the collective transport of Budapest and more than half of the long-distance bus transport of the companies Volán may stand.
At the same time, half the roads will be closed in many parts of the country.
Numerous trade unions and civil organizations have joined the strike, their names are constantly updated on the League's website.
Some unions announced their strike for indefinite time, others for definite time.
Until the afternoon of Thursday the State Railway and the Free Trade Union of Railway Workers (SLTF) could not reach an agreement even on the minimum services, although, as the Christmas holidays approach, more and more people travel on the trains.
According to information received so far, from the start of the day until 1 p.m. the workers of the Collective Transport Company of Budapest, the Budapest Airports from 7 a.m. to 9 a.m., will hold a four-hour strike the LIGA Trade Unions of the Electrical Industry and Thermal Energy, the Unions of Educators called for a 2-hour strike and the Democratic Union of Educators from 2 to 8 hours.
The Hungarian Association of Physicians will take a national strike in alternative hours and the Democratic Union of Health and Social Workers (SDTSSS) that are part of the Forum for Trade Union Cooperation will hold a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands made by the League is that the government withdraw its proposal for public health reform and submit a new concept to a social debate.
The second demand is that they gradually introduce the new form of pension calculation that will come into force next year.
The third is to ensure, even before 2010, that in the case of advanced pensions the possibility that the occupations that deserve it can enter the system.
The fourth reason for the strike is that the Free Trade Union of Railway Workers (SLTF) which is part of the League Unions, do not accept the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport on the railway side lines and expect another different proposal.
Political Capital[b1]: The Hungarian Guard increases the risk in the country
According to the Risk Analysis Division (Risk Analysis Division) of the Political Capital the activity of the Hungarian Guard, constituted in August of this year with the support of the Movement for a Better Hungary, from several points of view has increased the political risk of Hungary and the region.
In the company's "risk warning" it is written: in relation to the Hungarian Guard's activity the greatest political risk is the fact that "with the worsening of ethnic tensions between the Roma and non-Gypsy population in Hungary, even in the short term violent ethnic confrontations may occur".
The main reason for this is that the political strategy of the Hungarian Guard is probably the provocation of such an event - the representative of the research institute added.
They stated that all this is due to one of the main shortcomings of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: "the protagonists of public life gave the public debate of the Roma problem to the representatives of radical and extremist political groups, who were able to base their political strategy on the existing discrepancies between Gypsies and Hungarians".
This exacerbates the problem, makes normal dialogue impossible, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of violent conflict erupting - they estimate.
In addition, according to the research institute, the activity of the National Guard, as a result of the great attention of the national and international media, "has significantly deteriorated the image of Hungary abroad, especially with regard to the stability and democratic development of the country".
We are reminded that since the autumn of 2006 the reorganization of the radical and extreme right-wing groups in Hungary has received increasing publicity and impetus and that since the summer of 2007 numerous organizations have been formed in Hungary that define themselves as "national self-defence associations".
"The common feature of these groups is that they define themselves as civil organizations, while openly proclaiming the training of their members for defence - even armed - (civil defense, national defense, defense of public order), alluding to the ineptitudes of the police, the army, that is, the state" - they add.
They said: all this is done in accordance with the method that tries to give a civil presentation to different political aspirations, based on the discontent of society with politics and with political parties.
