The discussions in Baden, near Vienna, were the sixth and final session of negotiations since the troika was entrusted with a new mediation by the UN last August.
The US and Europeans consider that their mediation will end on 10 December.
The Russians, who have already blocked the granting of independence in Kosovo in the Security Council, insist on the pursuit of negotiations beyond that date.
" Russia was and is committed to a negotiated solution, a compromise solution, " said Botsane-Khartchenko.
