Serbian President Boris Tadic, for his part, considered that a compromise was always feasible, warning the Albanian majority of Kosovo against the consequences of a unilateral proclamation of the independence of the province.
Belgrade particularly fears a " domino effect " in a region still weakened by the wars of independence of the 1990s.
" For Serbia, " he said, "this does not mean that a commitment is impossible. "
On Tuesday, the Serbian delegation had insisted that any decision should belong exclusively to the Security Council, in which its Russian ally had a veto right.
" The Parliament of Kosovo will have the last word "
" Only a solution within the Security Council is acceptable to Serbia, " said Serbian Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica.
" These negotiations have lasted two years.
