How safe is it for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the event of possible accidents, involves a significant expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, the age of the card, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or the use of it, among others.
Having the car is only the beginning.
And it is that, choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insured.
This commitment is embodied in an insurance contract, which provides that the company receives the value of the agreed premium in exchange for being held liable for the obligation to pay damages in the event of a loss.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, the age of the card, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use given to it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so that in the most likely event of an accident, higher fees to be paid.
It is for this reason that both older than 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower rate of injury due to their prudence.
In addition, the companies have come to the conclusion that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use given to the vehicle will influence the frequency, and thus the probability of having some kind of perchance.
As the frequency increases, the odds increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
That is why the driver has to study the situation well in order to choose the car insurance that best fits his profile.
Here we will show the most significant variables when choosing one or another type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insured, offers you a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 have a number of disadvantages in hiring insurance at an affordable price, such as reduced driving experience and seniority of the card.
Although the ideal to be well insured is insurance at all risk, there are other more economical options.
The most cautious drivers can opt for a whole risk with franchise, so that they get insurance coverage at all risk but at a more feasible price.
This kind of agreement would mean that the client pays part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the amount of the damage that the customer contributes will be pre-set according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount," specifies Luis Noguera, Spain's highest responsible First Europe insurance broker.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer ensures protection against damage caused to third parties, although not to those caused in his own car.
In addition, it would be covered by theft, fire and vehicle loss.
A piece of advice.
If you are under the age of 25 try to be careful and avoid accidents as much as possible, as this will impact on the bonus, and can reduce the cost of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a discount on the basic fee that the company owns.
On the contrary, a penalty is a surcharge on that basic fee.
"The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and the benefit of it.
If the company has had a good year it can afford to increase the bonuses," explains Noguera.
After the 25-year-old age, drivers have it easier when they hire insurance, since the rate of injury is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
For this reason, it is most advisable to hire a whole risk with franchise.
"Young people usually cannot make use of the experience they have previously gained when using an accident, and even when driving," says the director in Spain of the European company, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, once the 'fear of the rookie' has passed.
However, if the client is married but still has no children, it is preferable for him to negotiate insurance at all risk, as long as his economic situation permits, of course.
For their part, marriages with children are considered by insurers as the public with the lowest rate of sinisterity, so the surcharges will be lower.
In this case the best insurance would be one at all risk with franchise (which could be 300 euros), or, when a high level of bonus is available, one to third parties extended from the third year of life of the vehicle.
"They carry out a more relaxed driving and have greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of taking on a larger amount of franchise," says Luis Noguera.
For retirees it is recommended to have an insurance at all risk with a franchise (this being 150 euros), or one to an extended third party when there is a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible accidents, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is why it is essential to study properly the insurance that suits us best according to our personal situation.
