In 2003 the financial district in Manila was a site that attracted all attention to the riot that was attempted against Arroyo.
The uprising failed after about 24 hours because the army wanted to participate.
Since 1986, there have been at least seven attempts at coups against the democratically elected government in the Philippines.
United Internet will be the largest shareholder in Versatel.
United Internet secured more than 20 percent of the shares of the Versatel telecommunications company.
On Wednesday the company reported that the average price for a share is 14, 46 euros.
It has only 20.05 percent of the share capital.
There was a lot of speculation about the company's absorption.
There are also options to further increase the financial share in Versatel.
United Internet reported that with this step it wants to accelerate the consolidation of the German market of DSL (digital subscription line).
On Wednesday they already made assumptions about entry into the business, after the Brendenberg bank increased its participation to the Duesseldorf network operator by 5 percent to 15.1 percent.
In the financial market this means that the financial institution maintains the securities of participation for a third party partner.
United Internet already the day before involved with almost 10 percent of the company of telecommunications Drillisch.
Drillisch in the measure of capital expansion placed 17,4 million of the new shares that have a value of 106,4 million euros.
United Internet has bought from them 5.15 million shares for 31.4 million euros.
In addition, companies began negotiations on DSL-products marketing cooperation.
"We strengthen our collaboration," said United Internet spokesperson.
The two companies founded an MSP joint venture to acquire the Freenet competitor.
On Thursday United Internet reported that at first, the two companies want to be happy with the ten percent stake in Freenet and do not make use of their right, i.e. 18.49 percent stake in Freenet.
That meant that both companies maintained all options, especially participation in the Freenet public limited company.
Negotiations between United Internet and Freenet on a strategic partnership ended in mid-November.
This "game" with Freenet that will last for many months and is not very understandable is part of the consolidation of the German Telecom market.
By the end of the third quarter Freenet had 2.9 million customers with a mobile phone contract and 1.27 million with a DSL contract or a full contract.
Until now United Internet and Drillisch's holding had directly 6.01 percent of Freenet's stake.
Then they had agreed that Drillisch would get the other four percent.
